in the radio broadcast.

30
00:02:26.073 --> 00:02:31.095
De Forest wanted to increase
the value of his patents, and

31
00:02:31.095 --> 00:02:36.540
he really believed that he owned
that particular technology.

32
00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:43.770
So at that time Edwin Armstrong
was a student at Columbia.

33
00:02:43.770 --> 00:02:48.760
And he understood
the operation of triode much

34
00:02:48.760 --> 00:02:53.810
better than De Forest or anybody else.

35
00:02:53.810 --> 00:02:58.230
