By 1922, RCA had paid Armstrong
a lot of royalties and

42
00:03:30.681 --> 00:03:36.689
starts that he had become a millionaire.

43
00:03:36.689 --> 00:03:43.258
And this was when the legal
battles between De Forest and

44
00:03:43.258 --> 00:03:47.871
Armstrong were really heating up, and

45
00:03:47.871 --> 00:03:54.300
essentially they ruined
both of them financially.

46
00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:59.355
And these were some of
the documents that were

47
00:03:59.355 --> 00:04:04.822
actually used in
the 20-year court battles.

48
00:04:04.822 --> 00:04:09.431
And around this time,
actually around 1913,

49
00:04:09.431 --> 00:04:13.289
when he was beginning his work with radio,

50
00:04:13.289 --> 00:04:18.217
he met another giant in the industry,
David Sarnoff,

51
00:04:18.217 --> 00:04:22.737
who was at that time working
at Marconi Wireless.

52
00:04:25.359 --> 00:04:28.340
Sarnoff and Armstrong had, again,

53
00:04:28.340 --> 00:04:33.380
a very long tumultuous relationship for
a long time.

54
00:04:33.380 --> 00:04:39.171
Sarnoff was interested in
the inventions by Armstrong mainly for

55
00:04:39.171 --> 00:04:44.539
radio applications,
